{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They just disappeared-- to and pick up their wife and family and save them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my husband remained as a lieutenant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was in charge of his whole battalion and was told by the French radio to leave their arm, leave all your armament intact and flee.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he never fled, never left his armament intact.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They took-- they used everything they could until they were surrounded and they could do no more.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's a very-- it's a really easy recollection, because I was married in January 1934.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We left for-- for Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were on our honeymoon for about six weeks, and we got back to Paris.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And during-- during the time that we had been gone, there had been terrible strikes in France, and there was a terrible- a terrible movement from the workers against-- against their employer.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what we found in coming back was a tremendous turmoil in France.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as we went from 1934 to 1939, this is my first five years of married life, where we never had a life because Leon Blum became the first Jewish prime minister, and that never happened in France before.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was a socialist, so that France became together a socialist and also-- and also led by a Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this didn't create any good feeding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, there was a lot of riots and a lot of-- a lot of turmoil.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in 1938, Chamberlain went to Germany and made a pact with Hitler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when he came back from-- from it, from England-- from Germany to England-- he picked up the radio and said to the world, I have avoided war for the last-- for the end of a century.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
